              "id": "68",
              "title": "Organisation update about Product - Advertising Platforms and Innovation",
              "publishedDate": "2024-11-14",
              "modalContent": {
                "Text": "<h3>A Message from Sanjay Bhakta</h3><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">As the needs of our business and customers continue to change, I have reviewed our functional alignment to ensure that Technology is organised most effectively for us to achieve success at Condé Nast.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">As a strategic priority, we want to accelerate our focus on growing our largest revenue stream and innovating in the Advertising Product space. To develop this priority, I have decided to hire a leader who has extensive experience in the development of digital advertising experiences and product capabilities, building high-performing product teams and driving cross-functional synergies in media companies.&nbsp; They will partner with the Commercial Team as senior strategic product leader on the future roadmap for all Commercial products.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">I am delighted to confirm that <strong>Thomas Greaney</strong> will join my leadership team on <strong>December 2nd as SVP, Product - Advertising Platforms and Innovation, </strong>based in our One World Trade Center Headquarters. Thomas is an experienced leader with strong product development expertise across media revenue lines, particularly in advertising and subscription products. Thomas joins us from Business Insider where he leads a multi-faceted organization.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Anthony Torres, Director will report to Thomas, and Anthony’s Ad Platforms &amp; Innovation team moving with him.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong>Katharine Bailey - SVP Product &amp; Design</strong> will continue to lead our overall Product &amp; Design strategic plans for Technology to connect our customers with our iconic brands through exceptional products, features, capabilities, and design.&nbsp;</span><br>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">The Product teams led by <strong>Ross Arbes, VP Product Consumer Revenue </strong>and<strong> Charl Porter, VP Product Data Products </strong>will continue to push enterprise value and dynamic revenue experiences with input from Thomas, as we focus on putting our customers first and more effectively monetize their visits to our products.&nbsp;</span><br>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Please do not hesitate to reach out to me or one of my leadership team if you have any questions and be sure to extend a warm welcome to Thomas when he joins us in early December.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Thanks</span></p><p><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Calibri, sans-serif;\">Sanjay</span></p>",
                "modalTitle": null,
                "media":{
                  "data":{
                    attributes:"Black"
                  }
                }
              }
